|YKOSigils are arcane markings worked into rare equipment.
Each marking carries a level, and while you wield, wear, or internally bind the item its
levels count toward your total for that sigil. Marked pieces work as a
set: equip several and their levels add together, up to the sigil's
maximum useful level.

Sigils are part of an item as it is found - you cannot inscribe them
yourself. Examine a piece of equipment to see any markings it bears,
each listed with its level and that sigil's maximum.

|WKBThe known sigils:|YKO
  Critical Strike  (max 5)  Increases your chance to land critical
                            hits.
  Evade            (max 5)  Increases your chance to evade hits.
  Ruthless         (max 7)  Extra combat damage to enemies based on
                            their missing health; higher levels work
                            against healthier enemies and hit harder.

Type |YKBsigils|YKO for a table of your active sigils: each combined
level against its maximum, and which piece of equipment supplies it.
The columns are head (H), cloak (C), shoulders (Sh), aura (A), neck
(N1/N2), body (B), legs (L), shield (S), feet (F), rings (R1/R2),
gloves (G), main and secondary weapons (MW/SW), internal equipment (I),
and other sources (O).
A total shown in bright color has reached that sigil's maximum.

